Merge pull request #4 from TRON-Bioinformatics/mutect2-RGSM-fix

Mutect2 added Funcotator annotation
remove all CPU parameters + add mutect2 args + add enable_bam_output + fixes issue with RG calculation
add test 6 which is ignored at the moment
Removed redundant parameter 'funcotator_db' and reset some previously set default values. Adjusted the config file accordingly.
Little bug fix related to wrong parameter declaration in the funcotator test.

Added the Funcotator tool from GATK optional to the pipeline with documentation and tests. The test does not work correctly, because the database is not uploaded to the repository and has to be setup first. This can be done through a simple download from GATK.

Added the parameter 'params.args_filter' to the filtering step, which can be supplied with custom options used by mutect2 FilterMutectCalls function. As default the minimum allele frequency is set to 5% '--min-allele-fraction 0.05', there has to be at least one read on both stands '--min-reads-per-strand 1' and at least 4 reads in total '--unique-alt-read-count 4' supporting the mutation call.

Merge pull request #3 from TRON-Bioinformatics/mutect2-RGSM-fix

Mutect2 rgsm fix
amend the checks on the RGSM + add tests
add checks on the input BAMs RGSM + fix an undetected bug

Fixed the replicate handling for the read group specification. Carefull: It will read out the RGSM from the first BAM file, since MUTECT2 only supports one input for the '--normal-sample', '--tumor-sample' arguments.
set both dependencies in the same conda directive
Added samtools to the conda environment.
Removed 1 accidentially copied line at the end of main.nf

Added support for custom naming of samples in the BAM readgroup SM. The sample now must not be named tumor or normal anymore. It reads the name out of the BAM. Make sure not to switch the tumor and normal column in the input file.
